               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17870523-37-person424">
                  ROBERT
                   WALLER
               <interp inst="t17870523-37-person424" type="surname" value="WALLER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17870523-37-person424" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17870523-37-person424" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>I live at <placeName id="t17870523-37-crimeloc194">the King's-head, in Love-lane, Thames-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17870523-37-crimeloc194" type="placeName" value="the King's-head, in Love-lane, Thames-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17870523-37-crimeloc194" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17870523-37-off192 t17870523-37-crimeloc194"></join>; on the 9th of May, I was going to start some liquor; I found the cup where I put some money in there, was missing; about eighteen or nineteen shillings out of a cupboard; in the parlour was the cupboard; I locked it; I turned the key in it and I thought it was locked; it appeared to me in the morning to have been picked; I put the key in it and the door was open.</p>
               <p>Did you miss the farthing? - No, I did not miss a farthing, I put the money into the cup just before I went to bed; when I missed the money, the prisoner came into the tap-room; he lodged in my house; he called for a penny-worth of purl; I asked him if Wenham was up; he said, yes; he was gone to Billinsgate, to attend the mackarel carts; I sent for him and told him I had been robbed; then says he, send for a constable and every one shall be searched; while some person was gone for the constable, some person threw some money under the table; I heard some money fall; there were eight or ten people in the room; they were sitting in a settle in the tap-room.</p>
               <p>How came the farthing in the indictment? - I do not know, only the farthing was picked up with the silver and half-pence off the ground.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17870523-37-person425">
                  THOMAS
                   PERROT
               <interp inst="t17870523-37-person425" type="surname" value="PERROT"></interp>
